<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/925716-throughout-the-series-words-are-used-that">Throughout the series, words are used that are no longer in use. I can guess a few from context or presumed sound, but I&#39;d like more help. Is there a resource for this vocabulary?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_925716'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F447892.An_Excellent_Mystery">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/925716-throughout-the-series-words-are-used-that">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/925716-throughout-the-series-words-are-used-that">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/20738920-orinoco-womble-tidy-bag-and-all"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1406361683i/20738920._UX100_CR0,18,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/20738920-orinoco-womble-tidy-bag-and-all">Orinoco Womble (tidy bag and all)</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Google&apos;s your friend. Many words can be defined by simply typing them into the searchbox; if not, try the online OED.<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Google's your friend. Many words can be defined by simply typing them into the searchbox; if not, try the online OED.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
