              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/82987855-moonkiszt?shelf=language-is-a-character">language-is-a-character</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/82987855-moonkiszt?shelf=topnotchmystery">topnotchmystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/82987855-moonkiszt?shelf=legends-myths-epics">legends-myths-epics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/82987855-moonkiszt?shelf=morphing-into-something-else">morphing-into-something-else</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/82987855-moonkiszt?shelf=setting-is-a-character">setting-is-a-character</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/82987855-moonkiszt?shelf=whodunit">whodunit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/82987855-moonkiszt?shelf=best-of-all-takin-with-me-top-favs">best-of-all-takin-with-me-top-favs</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4110067664" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3928911592737926788">Brother Cadfael is one my very favorite detectives. A Benedictine monk, and a Welsh-born man who had before being a monk fought in the Crusades, his heart is set on the countryside between England and Wales known as Shropshire and its environs. His years of detecting are in the 1100&apos;s, covering a period of 1137 through 1145. I read the whole series as they came out in the 70&apos;s-90&apos;s, and other than watching Sir Derek Jacobi on BCC wonderfully play this fine Brother, haven&apos;t been back to revisit.<br/><br/>I</span>
  <span id="freeText3928911592737926788" style="display:none">Brother Cadfael is one my very favorite detectives. A Benedictine monk, and a Welsh-born man who had before being a monk fought in the Crusades, his heart is set on the countryside between England and Wales known as Shropshire and its environs. His years of detecting are in the 1100's, covering a period of 1137 through 1145. I read the whole series as they came out in the 70's-90's, and other than watching Sir Derek Jacobi on BCC wonderfully play this fine Brother, haven't been back to revisit.<br /><br />I found a library audio copy of this one available and thought it was time to open that door of joy, and it was worth it. A great read with the kind of twist mystery readers love.<br /><br />As soon as my Nancy Drew reads are over, this will be my next series to go back to. Ellis Peters, a pen name for Edith Mary Pargeter, has left behind a boatload of excellent reads. Thankfully, she gave us the Chronicles of Brother Cadfael, among many others to keep us amused until we meet again.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3928911592737926788" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


